OL,3,CKing and Queen emerge from Tardis to
OL,4,Cbegin Glasgow Commonwealth Games
OL,6,FCharles formally opened the Games in
OL,7,Fhis role as Head of the Commonwealth,
OL,8,Fthe ceremonial leader of the
OL,9,Fassociation of 56 nations.
OL,11,FEarlier, the King attended a reception
OL,12,Fwhere he met baton bearers
OL,13,Frepresenting regions from across the
OL,14,FCommonwealth.
OL,16,FPrime Minister Andy Burnham and his
OL,17,Fwife, Marie-France Van Heel, also
OL,18,Fattended the reception, alongside
OL,19,FScottish First Minister John Swinney
OL,20,Fand the Duke of Edinburgh.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
